1
00:00:14,523 --> 00:00:16,275
Please hurry with the work.

2
00:00:16,581 --> 00:00:18,041
We’re chasing a deadline.

3
00:00:18,424 --> 00:00:19,432
Yes, sir.

4
00:00:19,464 --> 00:00:21,354
The cellphone
is missing.

5
00:00:21,379 --> 00:00:22,379
Huh?

6
00:00:22,928 --> 00:00:23,971
How did you lose it?

7
00:00:24,018 --> 00:00:25,018
Bank.

8
00:00:25,536 --> 00:00:26,537
Can we still do this?

9
00:00:28,044 --> 00:00:30,175
It’s almost 2 AM, and Pat
still hasn’t sent anything.

10
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:31,423
We’re out of time.

11
00:00:31,448 --> 00:00:33,466
If they can’t take
pictures of the exams,

12
00:00:33,491 --> 00:00:35,716
I’ll do it myself and find a way.

13
00:00:35,741 --> 00:00:38,886
I thought you guys were smart,
why didn’t you think of this?

14
00:00:39,493 --> 00:00:41,912
Out of all things,
you forget the breaker?

15
00:00:43,651 --> 00:00:45,027
Why’s there an electrician here?

16
00:00:45,052 --> 00:00:45,844
Sorry.

17
00:00:45,869 --> 00:00:49,373
But Boss Choi asked me to
say you’re not needed now.

18
00:00:49,398 --> 00:00:50,398
Ah, I see.

19
00:00:50,528 --> 00:00:53,635
Choi usually calls us for this stuff.

20
00:00:53,660 --> 00:00:54,952
You’ll see me in the window.

21
00:00:55,020 --> 00:00:56,730
Once I secure the test papers,

22
00:00:57,153 --> 00:00:58,487
I’ll give the go signal.

23
00:01:00,727 --> 00:01:01,737
Huh?

24
00:01:01,762 --> 00:01:03,057
I won't sign that.

25
00:01:03,804 --> 00:01:05,607
Not until I see your colleague.

26
00:01:09,365 --> 00:01:10,612
We got blocked by the guard.

27
00:01:10,637 --> 00:01:12,597
The phone was
on me the whole time,

28
00:01:12,622 --> 00:01:14,491
it was in my pocket
but I thought...

29
00:01:14,516 --> 00:01:15,925
I thought he saw it!

30
00:01:15,950 --> 00:01:16,950
Yes already!

31
00:01:17,285 --> 00:01:19,287
I paid the guard so
he would let me in

32
00:01:19,537 --> 00:01:22,040
and I paid him big so
he would let us out too.

33
00:01:22,155 --> 00:01:23,240
That was the plan B.

34
00:01:23,265 --> 00:01:24,267
Guys!

35
00:01:24,292 --> 00:01:26,186
There is something
wrong with the answers.

36
00:01:26,211 --> 00:01:28,797
We are missing one, two, three,

37
00:01:29,631 --> 00:01:31,222
six more items.

38
00:01:31,275 --> 00:01:33,455
Bank has photographic memory.

39
00:01:33,551 --> 00:01:35,386
If he can’t recite the answers,

40
00:01:35,457 --> 00:01:37,153
maybe he didn’t really answer at all.

41
00:01:37,263 --> 00:01:38,348
Just play along.

42
00:01:39,516 --> 00:01:40,809
You won’t lose anything.

43
00:01:41,949 --> 00:01:43,326
Just turn a
blind eye to this, Lin.

44
00:01:43,353 --> 00:01:44,996
We should've
just listened to Lin.

45
00:01:45,021 --> 00:01:47,690
We should've just stopped
and returned the money.

46
00:01:47,690 --> 00:01:49,234
I've made all the arrangements.

47
00:01:49,259 --> 00:01:50,802
You're going to the US.

48
00:01:50,985 --> 00:01:52,362
You'll study there.

49
00:01:52,487 --> 00:01:54,155
No. What about Grace?

50
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:56,824
It’s better if you break up.

51
00:01:57,371 --> 00:01:58,859
Please wait.

52
00:01:59,911 --> 00:02:01,037
Hold on a second.

53
00:02:02,214 --> 00:02:04,008
- What did you do?
- Sorry, Mom.

54
00:02:04,408 --> 00:02:05,986
Sorry, Mom.

55
00:02:11,761 --> 00:02:12,774
Grace.

56
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:13,842
Didn’t I tell you

57
00:02:14,092 --> 00:02:15,385
to stay away from her?

58
00:02:15,584 --> 00:02:16,584
Sis.

59
00:02:18,558 --> 00:02:21,589
I don't think you
need to leave Possenti.

60
00:02:43,893 --> 00:02:44,893
Hi.

61
00:02:46,419 --> 00:02:48,505
I hope that the auditorium

62
00:02:48,787 --> 00:02:52,422
gets done in time for
your batch's graduation.

63
00:02:53,243 --> 00:02:54,243
You know,

64
00:02:55,835 --> 00:02:57,809
I genuinely thought

65
00:02:58,002 --> 00:03:01,297
either you, or Tristan would
be valedictorian of your class.

66
00:03:02,950 --> 00:03:04,035
As it turns out,

67
00:03:06,382 --> 00:03:08,210
in the history of Possenti,

68
00:03:08,242 --> 00:03:09,242
the top

69
00:03:09,415 --> 00:03:10,777
students

70
00:03:10,802 --> 00:03:15,044
were also the ones who did the
most shameful act they could possibly do.

71
00:03:16,185 --> 00:03:17,853
Maybe in the next tournament,

72
00:03:18,220 --> 00:03:20,430
Possenti might also
make it to the championship

73
00:03:20,455 --> 00:03:22,416
if Lin plays.

74
00:03:30,429 --> 00:03:32,765
That is if you'll give her a chance

75
00:03:32,790 --> 00:03:35,000
to be a scholar of Possenti.

76
00:03:36,013 --> 00:03:38,379
Well, that's asking
for too much, Vin.

77
00:03:40,016 --> 00:03:41,042
I know.

78
00:03:41,131 --> 00:03:44,801
That’s why I’m thankful you
came so you could witness Lin.

79
00:03:45,273 --> 00:03:46,775
that she could be
the student to win

80
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,635
all of your academic competitions,

81
00:03:48,660 --> 00:03:50,745
if you give her a chance.

82
00:03:52,632 --> 00:03:53,755
You're right.

83
00:03:54,967 --> 00:03:56,635
I mean, she's highly intelligent.

84
00:03:58,743 --> 00:04:00,995
I would like to ask
for your forgiveness.

85
00:04:02,028 --> 00:04:04,113
I'm truly sorry for
everything that happened.

86
00:04:05,046 --> 00:04:07,257
You could expel me, but...

87
00:04:07,558 --> 00:04:08,558
you didn't.

88
00:04:08,690 --> 00:04:09,690
Right.

89
00:04:11,306 --> 00:04:14,267
You should also be punished
like what happened to Tristan.

90
00:04:15,086 --> 00:04:16,087
But,

91
00:04:16,827 --> 00:04:18,216
you have shown remorse.

92
00:04:18,319 --> 00:04:20,034
You surrendered
to the authorities.

93
00:04:20,845 --> 00:04:22,346
Which brings me to my point.

94
00:04:23,783 --> 00:04:26,869
I think, you don’t
need to leave Possenti.

95
00:04:28,162 --> 00:04:29,644
But I need your help.

96
00:04:31,130 --> 00:04:32,130
What is that?

97
00:04:34,225 --> 00:04:35,225
This year,

98
00:04:36,176 --> 00:04:39,032
applications opened

99
00:04:39,563 --> 00:04:42,136
for Alami-Khatib Scholarship.

100
00:04:42,617 --> 00:04:44,762
This only happens
every two years

101
00:04:45,114 --> 00:04:46,443
for applicants.

102
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:50,670
In my opinion, this is the
most difficult scholarship

103
00:04:50,756 --> 00:04:51,960
compared to all.

104
00:04:52,844 --> 00:04:58,569
You will be competing against
students from all over Southeast Asia.

105
00:05:00,941 --> 00:05:01,941
And,

106
00:05:03,977 --> 00:05:06,702
Lin, I think you’re the
only one who can win this

107
00:05:07,055 --> 00:05:08,139
in the whole school.

108
00:06:08,273 --> 00:06:09,995
Bank, a letter for you.

109
00:06:22,142 --> 00:06:23,310
Dear Bank,

110
00:06:23,335 --> 00:06:25,963
I was planning on telling
you this in person.

111
00:06:26,184 --> 00:06:29,286
but I know you don't
want to see me right now.

112
00:06:30,266 --> 00:06:32,810
I recently read one
of Nietzsche's book.

113
00:06:33,180 --> 00:06:34,765
There goes a quote, saying...

114
00:06:35,061 --> 00:06:37,104
He who fights with monsters

115
00:06:37,129 --> 00:06:39,799
might take care lest
he become a monster.

116
00:06:40,510 --> 00:06:41,511
That's us.

117
00:06:41,872 --> 00:06:43,908
Together with Grace and Pat.

118
00:06:46,089 --> 00:06:47,089
But sis...

119
00:06:48,797 --> 00:06:50,017
That'd be the last, okay?

120
00:06:51,650 --> 00:06:54,028
We might not get
away with it next time.

121
00:06:54,465 --> 00:06:56,050
I need more time with Grace,

122
00:06:56,124 --> 00:06:59,555
more travel dates with her,
more time for basketball.

123
00:06:59,763 --> 00:07:01,806
And I can’t have that
if my grades are low.

124
00:07:03,881 --> 00:07:05,800
So I just wanna make sure—

125
00:07:08,404 --> 00:07:10,740
You’ll let me copy
again next semester, right?

126
00:07:21,667 --> 00:07:23,185
Of course, you’re a scholar.

127
00:07:23,593 --> 00:07:26,412
You don’t need tutorials
just to pass your exams.

128
00:07:26,971 --> 00:07:28,218
But what about the rest?

129
00:07:28,577 --> 00:07:31,246
They’re smart in other ways,
but they’ll fail.

130
00:07:31,271 --> 00:07:34,702
Their lives could be ruined
just because of one subject like calculus.

131
00:07:35,735 --> 00:07:37,296
Can you really blame them?

132
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,293
Just leave them alone.

133
00:07:41,713 --> 00:07:43,381
The system is cheating us.

134
00:07:44,589 --> 00:07:46,549
Because if Possenti accepts bribes,

135
00:07:46,654 --> 00:07:49,966
our miscellaneous fees can
reach one hundred thousand pesos,

136
00:07:50,029 --> 00:07:51,614
even though we’re scholars.

137
00:07:53,639 --> 00:07:55,641
The school was the first to cheat us.

138
00:07:56,150 --> 00:07:59,312
Because of our thirst for revenge
on a rotten system,

139
00:07:59,696 --> 00:08:01,532
we became rotten ourselves.

140
00:08:01,557 --> 00:08:03,303
They wanted to cheat, right?

141
00:08:03,541 --> 00:08:06,252
They should accept the fact
that they'll be cheated too.

142
00:08:06,515 --> 00:08:09,884
I’ll memorize all the answers
then I’ll send them to you.

143
00:08:10,198 --> 00:08:11,478
Didn’t you already
take the exam?

144
00:08:12,328 --> 00:08:14,078
Can you memorize all of that?

145
00:08:14,317 --> 00:08:16,688
I can, if I have enough time.

146
00:08:17,105 --> 00:08:18,856
I tested it with
the remaining time

147
00:08:18,881 --> 00:08:21,105
I was able to memorize
half of the exam.

148
00:08:21,331 --> 00:08:22,596
That means,

149
00:08:23,137 --> 00:08:24,805
I can’t do this alone.

150
00:08:27,089 --> 00:08:28,841
Someone has to help me.

151
00:08:29,097 --> 00:08:30,968
So you need someone else.

152
00:08:33,579 --> 00:08:35,581
Who else is as smart as you?

153
00:08:38,383 --> 00:08:39,635
We need your help.

154
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:42,505
We have a new plan.

155
00:08:44,935 --> 00:08:46,059
What's the plan?

156
00:08:47,499 --> 00:08:49,919
The National College Entrance Test.

157
00:08:50,491 --> 00:08:51,651
NCET?

158
00:08:52,792 --> 00:08:53,792
NCET.

159
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:56,160
There will be more clients.

160
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:59,029
Because the whole Philippines
will be taking that test.

161
00:08:59,438 --> 00:09:01,504
Our lives are falling apart.

162
00:09:04,509 --> 00:09:07,220
I'd rather go broke
than go back to my dad.

163
00:09:07,650 --> 00:09:09,946
We're going to steal documents.

164
00:09:11,570 --> 00:09:15,034
One small mistake and
for sure, we'll end up in jail.

165
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:17,038
That's why I decided to come clean.

166
00:09:17,776 --> 00:09:20,362
That's the only way for this to end.

167
00:09:21,548 --> 00:09:23,552
I thought I made the right choice.

168
00:09:24,191 --> 00:09:26,445
But was my choice right for everyone?

169
00:09:27,238 --> 00:09:31,936
Even though all of us were wrong,
you're the one that suffered the most.

170
00:09:50,401 --> 00:09:51,411
Thank you, Grace.

171
00:09:51,436 --> 00:09:53,730
We'll post the results tomorrow.

172
00:09:54,087 --> 00:09:55,880
Okay. Thank you.

173
00:09:56,043 --> 00:09:57,043
Thank you.

174
00:10:03,034 --> 00:10:04,285
Grace is kinda good.

175
00:10:05,113 --> 00:10:08,450
Too bad, Sherry's parents are
expecting her to be the lead.

176
00:10:08,475 --> 00:10:11,186
They might pull their
donations out for the theater.

177
00:10:11,692 --> 00:10:15,042
Maybe we can ask Grace's family
for donations?

178
00:10:15,284 --> 00:10:17,536
They own a chain of
printing press, right?

179
00:10:17,983 --> 00:10:18,983
Yeah.

180
00:10:19,134 --> 00:10:21,802
You can ask her dad for donations.

181
00:10:23,898 --> 00:10:24,898
Claire!

182
00:10:28,165 --> 00:10:30,039
We had a deal, right?

183
00:10:30,438 --> 00:10:31,981
If I give you the test answer,

184
00:10:32,006 --> 00:10:35,375
you told me you will
not audition for the lead role.

185
00:10:35,556 --> 00:10:37,308
You offered first, Grace.

186
00:10:38,026 --> 00:10:40,022
You didn’t even give me a choice.

187
00:10:40,651 --> 00:10:42,033
You just thought we had a deal,

188
00:10:42,058 --> 00:10:43,684
but did you ever hear me say yes?

189
00:10:44,016 --> 00:10:45,100
You traitor!

190
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:47,400
Really?

191
00:10:48,053 --> 00:10:49,763
That’s coming from you?

192
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:52,064
Don’t you feel bad for Lin?

193
00:10:52,896 --> 00:10:53,969
Or Pat?

194
00:10:54,036 --> 00:10:55,245
Your boyfriend?

195
00:10:56,511 --> 00:10:59,306
You lied to them just
to get the lead part?

196
00:11:02,839 --> 00:11:05,133
We can justify our actions,

197
00:11:05,517 --> 00:11:08,079
there are lot's of reasons
why people cheat.

198
00:11:08,339 --> 00:11:09,627
If you feel burdened,

199
00:11:10,142 --> 00:11:12,061
you'll start to look
for the easier way.

200
00:11:21,067 --> 00:11:22,067
Hey, man.

201
00:11:23,276 --> 00:11:24,934
If you need help
with your report.

202
00:11:25,153 --> 00:11:28,086
You can just pay a guy,
to write it for you.

203
00:11:29,191 --> 00:11:30,191
I know someone.

204
00:11:30,659 --> 00:11:31,659
You want his number?

205
00:11:31,772 --> 00:11:33,526
Sometimes, I think...

206
00:11:34,305 --> 00:11:36,515
there's no end to this cheating.

207
00:11:37,843 --> 00:11:39,189
It's a cycle.

208
00:11:39,739 --> 00:11:41,103
If you get cheated,

209
00:11:41,566 --> 00:11:42,692
you'll cheat in return.

210
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:45,490
But is this how it’s going to be?

211
00:12:08,077 --> 00:12:10,037
Ma’am, please buy some.

212
00:12:10,062 --> 00:12:11,313
Sampaguita.

213
00:12:11,379 --> 00:12:12,379
Okay, give me two.

214
00:12:14,371 --> 00:12:15,525
Thank you.

215
00:12:25,317 --> 00:12:27,944
But you know what?
I still have so many questions.

216
00:12:27,969 --> 00:12:31,733
But earlier at school, when
I talked to Ma’am Perez,

217
00:12:31,946 --> 00:12:34,261
I also found the answer
I was looking for.

218
00:12:34,368 --> 00:12:37,800
So, if I get the scholarship,

219
00:12:38,614 --> 00:12:39,915
Possenti will be recognized

220
00:12:39,940 --> 00:12:41,202
under your term.

221
00:12:41,293 --> 00:12:42,827
You’ll benefit from it too.

222
00:12:42,852 --> 00:12:43,852
Is that right?

223
00:12:44,156 --> 00:12:46,921
Okay, I know what
you’re thinking.

224
00:12:47,693 --> 00:12:48,701
Lin, you know what?

225
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:50,186
That’s just how
the system works.

226
00:12:50,211 --> 00:12:52,008
This is how the world works.

227
00:12:55,140 --> 00:12:56,317
If that’s the case...

228
00:12:57,804 --> 00:12:59,839
Thank you, Ma'am Perez.

229
00:13:00,031 --> 00:13:01,057
Huh?

230
00:13:01,082 --> 00:13:02,878
What are you talking about?

231
00:13:03,599 --> 00:13:06,685
If you win this scholarship,
you get to study here

232
00:13:06,710 --> 00:13:07,710
and next year.

233
00:13:07,798 --> 00:13:11,274
Your dreams of studying
abroad will come true.

234
00:13:12,794 --> 00:13:14,210
Lin, come on.

235
00:13:15,251 --> 00:13:17,545
I’ve just made
my final decision.

236
00:13:17,808 --> 00:13:19,351
I don’t want to study
abroad anymore.

237
00:13:20,936 --> 00:13:25,399
And if, as you say, this
is how the system works,

238
00:13:26,380 --> 00:13:30,167
with all due respect,
I don’t want to be part of it.

239
00:13:34,265 --> 00:13:37,143
Bank, you might not
agree with me, as usual.

240
00:13:38,507 --> 00:13:40,114
Thank you, Ma’am Perez.

241
00:13:40,139 --> 00:13:43,643
But I think I made
the right decision.

242
00:13:49,379 --> 00:13:51,756
I haven’t apologized
to you personally.

243
00:13:54,614 --> 00:13:56,950
Sorry if you were the only
one who paid attention.

244
00:13:59,888 --> 00:14:02,960
Well, that’s just
how the system is.

245
00:14:03,855 --> 00:14:05,137
Of course, she has money.

246
00:14:11,781 --> 00:14:12,781
It’s okay, Lin.

247
00:14:13,699 --> 00:14:15,159
No one’s going
to pity me anyway.

248
00:14:17,322 --> 00:14:18,471
I’ve accepted it.

249
00:14:19,365 --> 00:14:21,185
There was really
nothing we could do.

250
00:14:24,747 --> 00:14:26,323
I just want to know one thing.

251
00:14:26,999 --> 00:14:28,677
If you could turn back time,

252
00:14:29,377 --> 00:14:31,720
would you still tell the
Education Commission

253
00:14:31,745 --> 00:14:33,545
the truth if you knew
this would happen to me?

254
00:14:40,063 --> 00:14:41,607
I’d still do it.

255
00:14:44,623 --> 00:14:46,104
Then why are you apologizing?

256
00:14:46,554 --> 00:14:47,909
Because I regret nothing.

257
00:14:50,513 --> 00:14:53,460
I’m not sorry for
doing what’s right.

258
00:14:54,706 --> 00:14:58,183
Maybe I’m sorry because I
couldn’t do anything to help you here.

259
00:14:59,208 --> 00:15:01,995
And with everything else
that’s happening to you,

260
00:15:05,414 --> 00:15:07,250
Your pity won't be of any help, Lin.

261
00:15:09,096 --> 00:15:10,639
Why are you here?

262
00:15:11,525 --> 00:15:14,070
Maybe I just wanted to
see if you’re still around.

263
00:15:15,968 --> 00:15:17,512
My friend Bank.

264
00:15:20,646 --> 00:15:23,148
Maybe I’ll miss
the old Bank too.

265
00:15:25,346 --> 00:15:28,933
The Bank who helped
that kid get his balloon back.

266
00:15:31,760 --> 00:15:32,760
I miss him.

267
00:15:34,479 --> 00:15:36,481
I miss the old Bank.

268
00:15:40,809 --> 00:15:44,324
I just really need that toy.
