00:30:06,066 --> 00:30:07,315
You won't get caught.

539
00:30:07,664 --> 00:30:08,828
I promise you.

540
00:30:10,555 --> 00:30:12,516
I'm used to always getting what I want.

541
00:30:13,258 --> 00:30:14,843
So, let's work smart.

542
00:30:15,085 --> 00:30:16,572
And let's work together.

543
00:30:26,441 --> 00:30:27,441
Eraser.

544
00:30:27,483 --> 00:30:28,483
Give it to me.

545
00:30:50,985 --> 00:30:52,194
What a waste of money.

546
00:30:53,194 --> 00:30:54,278
Please send it.

547
00:30:59,809 --> 00:31:00,906
Okay, got it.

548
00:31:08,765 --> 00:31:10,385
- What's taking so long!
- My gosh!

549
00:31:10,410 --> 00:31:11,006
Good luck, guys!

550
00:31:11,031 --> 00:31:13,795
And I learned the hard way that
if you want to achieve something,

551
00:31:13,877 --> 00:31:15,645
there are no shortcuts.

552
00:31:16,112 --> 00:31:19,735
You will retake the STIC and get,

553
00:31:19,760 --> 00:31:24,116
by studying, the high
marks that you got before.

554
00:31:24,258 --> 00:31:25,275
Or else...

555
00:31:25,300 --> 00:31:27,027
Or else you'll do what, Dad?

556
00:31:27,637 --> 00:31:30,628
Whatever I do, I am never enough for you.

557
00:31:31,764 --> 00:31:33,725
The phone was
on me the whole time

558
00:31:33,750 --> 00:31:37,503
it was in my pocket but I
thought, I thought he saw it!

559
00:31:37,858 --> 00:31:39,831
- You bastard, Bank! Huh!
- Stop! Enough!

560
00:31:39,856 --> 00:31:40,898
- Huh?
- Let go of me!

561
00:31:40,923 --> 00:31:43,591
Please, I didn’t want it to be like this.

562
00:31:43,689 --> 00:31:46,400
If you cheat, there
are no winners.

563
00:31:46,736 --> 00:31:47,945
And sometimes,

564
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:49,060
You're so messed up...

565
00:31:49,261 --> 00:31:51,673
you end up hurting
the people that you love.

566
00:31:52,278 --> 00:31:54,010
You cheated because I cheated?

567
00:31:56,681 --> 00:31:59,337
Out of all people, it’s Tony?

568
00:32:02,100 --> 00:32:04,922
But I have to grow up
and be responsible,

569
00:32:05,233 --> 00:32:07,819
disciplined and trustworthy.

570
00:32:15,633 --> 00:32:16,759
And most of all,

571
00:32:17,277 --> 00:32:19,810
and the person my dad can be proud of.

572
00:32:20,403 --> 00:32:21,953
- I love you hon.
- No more cheating.

573
00:32:22,793 --> 00:32:24,443
In relationships,

574
00:32:24,617 --> 00:32:26,702
in school and in work.

575
00:32:27,268 --> 00:32:29,436
what more when we become
managers and leaders someday?

576
00:32:29,846 --> 00:32:33,229
what more when we
become managers and leaders.

577
00:32:33,930 --> 00:32:34,930
I know someone.

578
00:32:35,478 --> 00:32:36,563
You want his number?

579
00:32:40,851 --> 00:32:42,103
I'll pass on that, dude.

580
00:32:42,415 --> 00:32:43,833
I'll try to do it myself.

581
00:32:44,937 --> 00:32:48,065
If I fail, it's all good.
At least I learned my lesson.

582
00:32:49,976 --> 00:32:50,976
Okay.

583
00:33:26,446 --> 00:33:28,657
I invited Pat and Grace
to help me,

584
00:33:28,682 --> 00:33:29,891
and they agreed.

585
00:33:31,450 --> 00:33:32,826
Really? They agreed?

586
00:33:35,311 --> 00:33:36,311
So, what's the plan?

587
00:33:37,695 --> 00:33:41,074
First of all, I’ll be
staying here for college.

588
00:33:41,938 --> 00:33:43,356
I’ll become a teacher,

589
00:33:44,256 --> 00:33:45,882
and when I graduate,

590
00:33:46,439 --> 00:33:48,283
I’ll work for the
Commission on Education.

591
00:33:49,510 --> 00:33:51,679
At least one of us
should get in there.

592
00:33:52,539 --> 00:33:54,717
Pat and Grace, on the
other hand, will sponsor

593
00:33:54,741 --> 00:33:57,233
a free tutorial program
for out-of-school youth

594
00:33:57,793 --> 00:33:59,308
using their network.

595
00:34:02,297 --> 00:34:03,548
As for you, Bank,

596
00:34:05,729 --> 00:34:08,254
I want you to study law.

597
00:34:09,196 --> 00:34:11,782
You can take Public Administration
as your pre-law.

598
00:34:14,672 --> 00:34:16,722
You want me to go
into public service?

599
00:34:17,880 --> 00:34:20,215
I cheated on the STIC
and NCET, remember?

600
00:34:23,017 --> 00:34:27,396
That’s exactly why.
You’re the smartest cheater.

601
00:34:29,813 --> 00:34:32,579
And maybe it takes
a good cheater

602
00:34:32,604 --> 00:34:36,816
to redesign a system without
cheating and corruption.

603
00:34:39,399 --> 00:34:43,438
All that corruption should
stop with our generation, right?

604
00:34:46,420 --> 00:34:48,631
Okay, visiting hours are over.

605
00:34:48,788 --> 00:34:50,672
Bank, let’s go back inside.

606
00:34:52,826 --> 00:34:54,328
The decision is yours, Bank.

607
00:35:03,492 --> 00:35:05,786
It wasn’t hard to
answer Lin’s question.

608
00:35:07,358 --> 00:35:08,693
Because no matter
how smart you are…

609
00:35:08,718 --> 00:35:10,195
Colegio de San Gabriel Possenti?

610
00:35:10,905 --> 00:35:14,784
3.14159265358979.

611
00:35:15,111 --> 00:35:18,531
We're rivals for the scholarship
until we graduate.

612
00:35:19,427 --> 00:35:21,262
So someone will win,
someone will lose.

613
00:35:21,826 --> 00:35:22,868
Deal with it.

614
00:35:23,762 --> 00:35:27,213
No matter how hard you consider
all the variables,

615
00:35:29,233 --> 00:35:31,027
your heart will
always win in the end.

616
00:35:31,959 --> 00:35:34,920
If we just learn to listen to
what our hearts are saying,

617
00:35:36,195 --> 00:35:38,356
we can make the right choices.

618
00:35:54,744 --> 00:35:56,261
Thank you, Doc.

619
00:35:57,854 --> 00:36:00,214
It feels so good to the ears, right?

620
00:36:01,952 --> 00:36:03,412
Doctor...

621
00:36:03,525 --> 00:36:04,568
Bangkat.

622
00:36:05,001 --> 00:36:06,847
But what ruled me
instead were anger,

623
00:36:07,754 --> 00:36:08,754
envy,

624
00:36:09,143 --> 00:36:12,188
and the desire to outsmart the
system that made our lives difficult.

625
00:36:13,542 --> 00:36:15,044
I chose the wrong path.

626
00:36:15,649 --> 00:36:16,649
And in the end,

627
00:36:17,101 --> 00:36:20,136
I became no different from
the people I used to despise.

628
00:36:26,273 --> 00:36:28,525
I’m sorry to disappoint you, Ma’am, but…

629
00:36:32,855 --> 00:36:33,898
Starting today,

630
00:36:34,445 --> 00:36:37,657
I won’t let my intelligence be used
for the wrong reasons anymore—

631
00:36:38,511 --> 00:36:40,211
for deceiving others.

632
00:36:41,415 --> 00:36:43,478
Hold on a second.

633
00:36:43,810 --> 00:36:45,966
- What did you do?
- Sorry, Mom.

634
00:36:45,991 --> 00:36:47,538
Sorry, Mom.

635
00:36:47,563 --> 00:36:48,731
Don't worry, Tristan.

636
00:36:48,822 --> 00:36:51,979
Tristan, I’ll get a good lawyer.

637
00:36:52,004 --> 00:36:53,339
I won’t abandon you.

638
00:36:53,364 --> 00:36:55,725
Remember that.
I’m right here.

639
00:36:55,755 --> 00:36:57,214
Come on now, come with us.

640
00:36:57,214 --> 00:37:00,051
- Please wait.
- Mom, don’t leave me.

641
00:37:00,076 --> 00:37:01,255
Come now, come with us.

642
00:37:01,280 --> 00:37:02,303
Come now, come on!

643
00:37:02,303 --> 00:37:03,846
- Mom!
- Wait! Wait!

644
00:37:03,871 --> 00:37:04,914
Mom!

645
00:37:05,181 --> 00:37:06,933
Mom, no! Come with me!

646
00:37:07,433 --> 00:37:08,433
Mom!

647
00:37:15,048 --> 00:37:16,048
No, Mom.

648
00:37:17,547 --> 00:37:18,686
I’ll make it up to you.

649
00:37:22,863 --> 00:37:25,006
I’ll still give you a good life,

650
00:37:25,124 --> 00:37:26,587
no matter what happens.

651
00:37:28,519 --> 00:37:30,940
And if I achieve the dreams
Mom and I once shared,

652
00:37:32,295 --> 00:37:35,048
I’ll proudly say I
earned it the right way.

653
00:37:39,101 --> 00:37:41,770
I wouldn’t have learned
this if it weren’t for Grace,

654
00:37:42,142 --> 00:37:43,152
Pat,

655
00:37:43,177 --> 00:37:44,177
and most of all,

656
00:37:44,528 --> 00:37:45,528
Lin.

657
00:37:46,873 --> 00:37:48,457
We’re just both finding ways

658
00:37:48,482 --> 00:37:50,581
to change our situation, right?

659
00:37:52,968 --> 00:37:56,638
Life in the Philippines is
hard if you’re not born rich.

660
00:37:57,855 --> 00:38:00,096
But are we just
going to give up?

661
00:38:01,021 --> 00:38:03,080
Of course not—we’ll
just work harder, right?

662
00:38:03,592 --> 00:38:05,533
That’s our fight now.

663
00:38:08,092 --> 00:38:09,464
I never thought that

664
00:38:09,557 --> 00:38:12,058
the reason for my
first trip abroad is

665
00:38:12,238 --> 00:38:14,678
because I’m an accomplice in
an international cheating scheme.

666
00:38:14,703 --> 00:38:15,703
Hey!

667
00:39:44,094 --> 00:39:45,094
Like them,

668
00:39:45,382 --> 00:39:49,178
I chose to use the same
intelligence that set me free

669
00:39:49,883 --> 00:39:51,236
to help free others.

670
00:39:51,865 --> 00:39:52,908
Good, or bad,

671
00:39:53,742 --> 00:39:55,298
can be a genius.

672
00:39:56,183 --> 00:39:57,977
The choice is yours.
